<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2942> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2942" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the basis on Rossbach's restoration of Liv. Oxy. Per. 50, line 109, Niccolini (FTP 129) would date in this year the Atinian plebiscite{459} which made Tribunes regular members of the Senate ([... de tribunis pl.] lat[a est] 1[ex] At[inia]: cf. Gell. 14.8.2, which Rolfe [LCL 3.55, n.] attributes to the Tribune of 196). Niccolini also attributes to this same Tribune the Lex Atinia de usucapione (Cic. Verr. 2.1.109; Phil. 3.16; Gell. 17.7.1; Ulp. in Dig. 41.3.4.6; Ps.-Ascon. 248 Stangl; cf. Gaius 2.45; Bruns FIR\n     47; Riccobono, Fontes 1.81, no. 4)." .
